\f0\b\fs22 \cf2 \ul \ulc2 EmoTracker 2.3.8.20\
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 \ulnone Service URL Configuration and Relocation\
\pard\pardeftab720\li576\fi-360\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 This release points the application at the new community service host, and supports configuring an alternative service URL via application_settings.json
\f0\b\fs22 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl252\slmult1\sb240\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \ulc3 EmoTracker 2.3.8.19\
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 \ulnone Developer-Facing Auto-Tracking Changes\
\pard\pardeftab720\li576\fi-360\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 This release addresses an issue that could cause memory watch updates to get starved when Lua callbacks took a very long time
\f0\b \

\f1\b0 This release also forcefully suspends logic updates during memory watch callbacks, which should not actually change behavior, but clarifies the behavior in the code.
\f0\b \
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl252\slmult1\sb240\sa120\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 EmoTracker 2.3.8.16\
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 \ulnone Auto-Tracking Changes\
\pard\pardeftab720\li576\fi-360\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 Auto-tracking no longer requires an internet connection, and no longer enforces memory access restrictions
\f0\b \

\f1\b0 ALTTPR was the only game that ever asked for restrictions, new modes are coming all the time that require additions to the access control list, and importantly, community sentiment has broadly settled on auto-tracking. As a result, I am removing this requirement, and deprecating the memory restriction system.
\f0\b \

\f1\b0 Users are 100% responsible for ensuring that any pack they are using meets the standards for auto-tracking set by their community if they are using it in a racing or otherwise competitive scenario.
\f0\b \
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
Minor Improvement to Save File Loading\
\pard\pardeftab720\li576\fi-360\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 Loading a save file will now allow items to be reordered, but will issue a warning in the developer console when doing so. Pack developers should work to eliminate these warnings, as they may cause issues for users in the future.
\f0\b \
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl252\slmult1\sb240\sa120\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 EmoTracker 2.3.8.15\
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 \ulnone Add ViewBox Layout Item Type\
\pard\pardeftab720\li576\fi-360\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 \'93viewbox\'94 can be used to auto-scale its content
\f0\b \
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
Force Invisibility Rules Fix\
\pard\pardeftab720\li576\fi-360\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 Force Invisibility rules for map locations were not applying properly to badges, etc.
\f0\b \
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl252\slmult1\sb240\sa120\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 EmoTracker 2.3.8.9\
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 \ulnone Minor Auto-Tracker Fix\
\pard\pardeftab720\li576\fi-360\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 Fix an issue with validating memory segments against 1-byte long approved ranges
\f0\b \
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
Badge Rendering Fixes & Improvements\
\pard\pardeftab720\li576\fi-360\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 Badge-sizing for locations was subtly broken, and this has been corrected
\f0\b \

\f1\b0 Custom badge sizes can be set on map locations via the \'93badge_size\'94 property
\f0\b \
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl252\slmult1\sb240\sa120\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 EmoTracker 2.3.8.7\
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 \ulnone Fix autotracking on Retroarch via qusb2snes\
\pard\pardeftab720\li576\fi-360\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 Qusb2snes is occasionally very dumb, and does things like decide to crash if you attempt to read from ROM addresses on Retroarch.
\f0\b \
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl252\slmult1\sb240\sa120\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 EmoTracker 2.3.8.6\
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 \ulnone Disable ConnectorLib address mapping\
\pard\pardeftab720\li576\fi-360\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 ConnectorLib\'92s new SNES address mapping functionality breaks SMZ3 autotracking support in extremely problematic ways. This patch disables this feature, which restores (AFAICT) proper functionality.
\f0\b \
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0 \cf0 ConnectorLib will eventually be removed from EmoTracker, to be replaced by a custom solution.
\f3\b \
\pard\pardeftab720\li216\ri216\sl252\slmult1\sb240\sa120\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0\fs22 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 EmoTracker 2.3.8.4\
